    Functional Interface:
    This is a functional interface and can therefore be used as the assignment target for a lambda expression or method reference.

    @FunctionalInterface
public interface ThrowingToBooleanFunction0
extends AbstractThrowingToBooleanFunction0<AbstractThrowingToBooleanFunction0.Handler>
    Represents a function that accepts no arguments and produces a boolean-valued result or throws a throwable. This is the zero-arity specialization of ThrowingToBooleanFunctionN. This is the boolean-producing primitive specialization of ThrowingFunction0. This is the throwing variation of ToBooleanFunction0.

    This is a functional interface whose functional method is AbstractThrowingToBooleanFunction0.applyAsBoolean().

    Since:
    1.0.0
